Pronotum longer than broad (length:width ratio 
1.1
); lateral margin subparallel, strongly constricted basally; glossy green to blue; coarsely punctate, anterior to transverse depression less coarsely punctate and sligthly obscure; with dark and pale pubescence.

Elytra almost two and a half times as long as broad (length:width ratio 
2.43
); lateral margin parallel; densely and deeply punctate, irregular; diameter of punctures two to three times larger than intervals, punctation at base finer; apex variable: bevelled and often acute with tooth, sometimes with several small teeth, or apex not bevelled and without tooth; sparse pubescence, composed of short, dark and pale hairs.
